<isis lang="en">
    <stitle>ELECTRICAL SYSTEM TROUBLESHOOTING GUIDE - 9800 - 6 SPEED TRANSMISSIONS SPICER PSO140-61 - DISASSEMBLE -
        COUNTERSHAFT
    </stitle>
    <svcsection/>
    <svcproc svcproctype="disassemble" graphiccount="4">
        <title>COUNTERSHAFT</title>
        <para>Refer to
            <hotlnk xrefid="f1301441">Figure 41</hotlnk>.
        </para>
        <figure id="f1301441" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic id="g1301441" filename="../figg13/g1301441.webp" type="webp" resolution="72"/>
            <caption>Figure 41. Countershaft Exploded View</caption>
        </figure>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">
                <hotlnk xrefid="f1301442">Figure 42</hotlnk>
                shows the hub direction of the gears. The first-reverse gear is an integral part of the shaft, while the
                remaining gears are secured with individual Woodruff keys under each gear.
            </para>
            <figure id="f1301442" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g1301442" filename="../figg13/g1301442.webp" type="webp" resolution="72"/>
                <caption>Figure 42. Hub Direction of Gears</caption>
            </figure>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">If you place a straight edge between these painted teeth, every gear on the countershaft
                will be in line (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f1301443">Figure 43</hotlnk>). When you set these shafts in time, these marks will be
                directly across from each other.
            </para>
            <figure id="f1301443" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g1301443" filename="../figg13/g1301443.webp" type="webp" resolution="72"/>
                <caption>Figure 43. Gears on Countershaft in Line</caption>
            </figure>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">The countershaft rear bearing requires a spacer ring for proper location (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f1301444">Figure 44</hotlnk>).
            </para>
            <figure id="f1301444" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g1301444" filename="../figg13/g1301444.webp" type="webp" resolution="72"/>
                <caption>Figure 44. Countershaft Rear Bearing Requires Spacer Ring</caption>
            </figure>
        </step1>
    </svcproc>
